HEADWORD: Undershapen
<hw>Un"der*shap`en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Under the usual
shape or size; small; dwarfish.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His dwarf, a vicious <qex>undershapen</qex> thing.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undersheriff</ent>⟦br⟧
